MACROS WITH ARGUMENTS

Writing programs with macros that have arguments can be both
frustrating and tedious.  The problem is that the preprocessor
rules are different from those of the compiler.

Modern programming methodology has moved away from using
macros with arguments.

The program we have written here illustrates the use of
macros with arguments.

